0.title: About
0.content: ETH Montreal is a community-driven initiative to connect our local projects, developers, students, researchers, and artists with the broader international Ethereum community. We place a strong emphasis on engaging students from our world-class universities and onboard them to the ecosystem. At its core, it is an annual hackathon and conference, but it has further ambitions as a support infrastructure for up-and-coming builders, researchers, and public-goods projects in Montreal.

1.title: Get involved
1.content: ETH Montréal is an open community and we welcome anyone wanting to be involved. You can also reach or follow us via our communication channels: . | Telegram . | Twitter . | Email . | Email updates . | .

5.title: Quick facts about the hackathon:
5.content: . | The whole event is free for hackers. | Hackers get to interact with mentors and project leaders from the Ethereum ecosystem. | As a hacker you can participate solo or in a group of hackers that you will meet in our community discord before the event. | There will be workshops and tutorials by project leaders, developers, researchers, and mentors from the wider global Ethereum community. | There will be prizes to the hackathon winners as decided by expert judges. | Hackathon winners will (among other perks) be invited to a special dinner after the event. | . We recommend applying with your organizational email (like a university email, we won’t spam) if you are a student or a junior developer . Proceed to the application ..    .
